<title>USA: L. Luria &amp; Son Q1 shr loss narrows.</title>
<headline>L. Luria &amp; Son Q1 shr loss narrows.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMI 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Period ended May 3</p>
<p>					  FY1998		     FY1997</p>
<p>    Net Sales		     $ 16,973		   $ 29,369</p>
<p>    Operating income (loss)     (2,978)		    (4,349)</p>
<p>    Net Income (Loss)	     (1,553)		    (7,400)</p>
<p>    Net Income (Loss) per shr     (.28)		     (1.35)</p>
<p>(all data above in 000s except per share)</p>
<p>NOTES: Full company name is L. Luria &amp; Son Inc.</p>
<p>The company said Q1 year ago results have been restated to reflect a change in accounting procedures. Before the charge, fiscal 1997 Q1 net loss would have been $3,014,000 or a share loss of $0.55.</p>
<p>The drop in net sales reflects sales from 15 fewer stores in Q1 fiscal 1998 than a year ago, it said.</p>
